#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="mn81"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn81:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 81 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 81 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn81:0.2"
msgid "Ghaṭikārasutta "
msgstr "With Ghaṭikāra "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, pts-vp-pli2.45, sc1
msgctxt "mn81:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn81:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosalesu cārikaṃ carati mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was wandering in the land of the Kosalans together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants. "

#. REF: nya2
msgctxt "mn81:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā maggā okkamma aññatarasmiṃ padese sitaṃ pātvākāsi. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha left the road, and at a certain spot he smiled. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:2.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato ānandassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Venerable Ānanda thought, "

msgctxt "mn81:2.3"
msgid "“ko nu kho hetu, ko paccayo bhagavato sitassa pātukammāya? "
msgstr "“What is the cause, what is the reason why the Buddha smiled? "

#. VAR: Na akāraṇena → na akāraṇe (bj)
msgctxt "mn81:2.4"
msgid "Na akāraṇena tathāgatā sitaṃ pātukarontī”ti. "
msgstr "Realized Ones do not smile for no reason.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: cīvaraṃ → uttarāsaṅgaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn81:2.5"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando ekaṃsaṃ cīvaraṃ katvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "So Ānanda got up from his seat, arranged his robe over one shoulder, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha, and said, "

msgctxt "mn81:2.6"
msgid "“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo bhagavato sitassa pātukammāya? "
msgstr "“What is the cause, what is the reason why the Buddha smiled? "

msgctxt "mn81:2.7"
msgid "Na akāraṇena tathāgatā sitaṃ pātukarontī”ti. "
msgstr "Realized Ones do not smile for no reason.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3
#. VAR: vegaḷiṅgaṃ → vehaliṅgaṃ (bj) | vebhaḷigaṃ (s1-3, km) | vebhaḷiṅgaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "mn81:3.1"
msgid "“Bhūtapubbaṃ, ānanda, imasmiṃ padese vegaḷiṅgaṃ nāma gāmanigamo ahosi iddho ceva phīto ca bahujano ākiṇṇamanusso. "
msgstr "“Once upon a time, Ānanda, there was a market town in this spot named Vebhaliṅga. It was successful and prosperous and full of people. "

msgctxt "mn81:3.2"
msgid "Vegaḷiṅgaṃ kho, ānanda, gāmanigamaṃ kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho upanissāya vihāsi. "
msgstr "And Kassapa, a blessed one, a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha, lived supported by Vebhaliṅga. "

msgctxt "mn81:3.3"
msgid "Idha sudaṃ, ānanda, kassapassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa ārāmo ahosi. "
msgstr "It was here, in fact, that he had his monastery, "

msgctxt "mn81:3.4"
msgid "Idha sudaṃ, ānanda, kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho nisinnako bhikkhusaṃghaṃ ovadatī”ti. "
msgstr "where he sat and advised the mendicant Saṅgha.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4
msgctxt "mn81:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando catugguṇaṃ saṅghāṭiṃ paññapetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Ānanda spread out his outer robe folded in four and said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "mn81:4.2"
msgid "“tena hi, bhante, bhagavā nisīdatu ettha. "
msgstr "“Well then, sir, may the Blessed One sit here! "

msgctxt "mn81:4.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ bhūmipadeso dvīhi arahantehi sammāsambuddhehi paribhutto bhavissatī”ti. "
msgstr "Then this piece of land will have been occupied by two perfected ones, fully awakened Buddhas.” "

msgctxt "mn81:4.4"
msgid "Nisīdi bhagavā paññatte āsane. "
msgstr "The Buddha sat on the seat spread out. "

msgctxt "mn81:4.5"
msgid "Nisajja kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "When he was seated he said to Venerable Ānanda: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya5, pts-vp-pli2.46, sc2
msgctxt "mn81:5.1"
msgid "“Bhūtapubbaṃ, ānanda, imasmiṃ padese vegaḷiṅgaṃ nāma gāmanigamo ahosi iddho ceva phīto ca bahujano ākiṇṇamanusso. "
msgstr "“Once upon a time, Ānanda, there was a market town in this spot named Vebhaliṅga. It was successful and prosperous and full of people. "

msgctxt "mn81:5.2"
msgid "Vegaḷiṅgaṃ kho, ānanda, gāmanigamaṃ kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho upanissāya vihāsi. "
msgstr "And Kassapa, a blessed one, a perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha, lived supported by Vebhaliṅga. "

msgctxt "mn81:5.3"
msgid "Idha sudaṃ, ānanda, kassapassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa ārāmo ahosi. "
msgstr "It was here, in fact, that he had his monastery, "

msgctxt "mn81:5.4"
msgid "Idha sudaṃ, ānanda, kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho nisinnako bhikkhusaṅghaṃ ovadati. "
msgstr "where he sat and advised the mendicant Saṅgha. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya6, sc3
#. VAR: ghaṭikāro → ghaṭīkāro (bj, s1, pts1)
msgctxt "mn81:6.1"
msgid "Vegaḷiṅge kho, ānanda, gāmanigame ghaṭikāro nāma kumbhakāro kassapassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa upaṭṭhāko ahosi aggupaṭṭhāko. "
msgstr "The Buddha Kassapa had as chief attendant in Vebhaliṅga a potter named Ghaṭīkāra. "

msgctxt "mn81:6.2"
msgid "Ghaṭikārassa kho, ānanda, kumbhakārassa jotipālo nāma māṇavo sahāyo ahosi piyasahāyo. "
msgstr "Ghaṭīkāra had a dear friend named Jotipāla, a brahmin student. "

msgctxt "mn81:6.3"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, ghaṭikāro kumbhakāro jotipālaṃ māṇavaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then Ghaṭīkāra addressed Jotipāla, "

msgctxt "mn81:6.4"
msgid "‘āyāma, samma jotipāla, kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissāma. "
msgstr "‘Come, dear Jotipāla, let’s go to see the Blessed One Kassapa, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha. "

# NOTE: sadhusammata is used elsewhere only as an epithet of (real or supposed) saints or holy men. It must therefore have a stronger sense than simply good. Obviously this refers to the ancient Indian idea of darsana, that simply the sight of holy me was a sacred blessing.
msgctxt "mn81:6.5"
msgid "Sādhusammatañhi me tassa bhagavato dassanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassā’ti. "
msgstr "For I regard it as holy to see that Blessed One.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:6.6"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, ānanda, jotipālo māṇavo ghaṭikāraṃ kumbhakāraṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, Jotipāla said to him, "

msgctxt "mn81:6.7"
msgid "‘alaṃ, samma ghaṭikāra. "
msgstr "‘Enough, dear Ghaṭīkāra. "

# NOTE: BB just has ascetic, but samanaka is always pejorative.
msgctxt "mn81:6.8"
msgid "Kiṃ pana tena muṇḍakena samaṇakena diṭṭhenā’ti? "
msgstr "What’s the use of seeing that baldy, that fake ascetic?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:6.9"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho, ānanda … pe … "
msgstr "For a second time … "

msgctxt "mn81:6.10"
msgid "tatiyampi kho, ānanda, ghaṭikāro kumbhakāro jotipālaṃ māṇavaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "and a third time, Ghaṭīkāra addressed Jotipāla, "

msgctxt "mn81:6.11"
msgid "‘āyāma, samma jotipāla, kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissāma. "
msgstr "‘Come, dear Jotipāla, let’s go to see the Blessed One Kassapa, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha. "

msgctxt "mn81:6.12"
msgid "Sādhusammatañhi me tassa bhagavato dassanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassā’ti. "
msgstr "For I regard it as holy to see that Blessed One.’ "

