#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:8.20"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, jotipālassa māṇavassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Jotipāla thought, "

msgctxt "mn81:8.21"
msgid "‘acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho. "
msgstr "‘It’s incredible, it’s amazing, "

msgctxt "mn81:8.22"
msgid "Yatra hi nāmāyaṃ ghaṭikāro kumbhakāro ittarajacco samāno amhākaṃ sīsaṃnhātānaṃ kesesu parāmasitabbaṃ maññissati; "
msgstr "how this potter Ghaṭikāra, though born in a lower caste, should presume to grab me by the hair of my freshly-washed head! "

msgctxt "mn81:8.23"
msgid "na vatidaṃ kira orakaṃ maññe bhavissatī’ti; "
msgstr "This must be no ordinary matter.’ "

msgctxt "mn81:8.24"
msgid "ghaṭikāraṃ kumbhakāraṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "He said to Ghaṭīkāra, "

# NOTE: Comm says “dokārahikārapikārā nipātā, yāvatuparimanti attho”, i.e. “the words do, hi, and pi are particles; the meanings is 'to this extent'. This is followed by all the translators I have checked (Bodhi, Horner, Chalmers) But dohi is “milking”, as in anavasesadohī "milk dry", an idiom which is used in the similar sense of "pushing the matter this far" in AN 11.7, etc. The English idiom "to milk" in the sense of "get all possible advantage from (a situation)" is similar enough that it is, i think, worth preserving the literal idiom.
#. VAR: yāvatādohipi → yāvetadohipi (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn81:8.25"
msgid "‘yāvatādohipi, samma ghaṭikārā’ti? "
msgstr "‘You’d even milk it to this extent, dear Ghaṭīkāra?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:8.26"
msgid "‘Yāvatādohipi, samma jotipāla. "
msgstr "‘I even milk it to this extent, dear Jotipāla. "

msgctxt "mn81:8.27"
msgid "Tathā hi pana me sādhusammataṃ tassa bhagavato dassanaṃ arahato sammāsambuddhassā’ti. "
msgstr "For that is how holy I regard it to see that Blessed One.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:8.28"
msgid "‘Tena hi, samma ghaṭikāra, muñca; gamissāmā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Well then, dear Ghaṭīkāra, release me, we shall go.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya10, sc5
msgctxt "mn81:10.1"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, ghaṭikāro ca kumbhakāro jotipālo ca māṇavo yena kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā ghaṭikāro kumbhakāro kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Jotipālo pana māṇavo kassapena bhagavatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena saddhiṃ sammodi. Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
msgstr "Then Ghaṭīkāra the potter and Jotipāla the brahmin student went to the Buddha Kassapa. Ghaṭīkāra bowed and sat down to one side, but Jotipāla exchanged greetings with the Buddha and sat down to one side. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:10.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho, ānanda, ghaṭikāro kumbhakāro kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Ghaṭīkāra said to the Buddha Kassapa, "

msgctxt "mn81:10.3"
msgid "‘ayaṃ me, bhante, jotipālo māṇavo sahāyo piyasahāyo. "
msgstr "‘Sir, this is my dear friend Jotipāla, a brahmin student. "

msgctxt "mn81:10.4"
msgid "Imassa bhagavā dhammaṃ desetū’ti. "
msgstr "Please teach him the Dhamma.’ "

msgctxt "mn81:10.5"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho ghaṭikārañca kumbhakāraṃ jotipālañca māṇavaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha Kassapa educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired Ghaṭikāra and Jotipāla with a Dhamma talk. "

msgctxt "mn81:10.6"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, ghaṭikāro ca kumbhakāro jotipālo ca māṇavo kassapena bhagavatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā kassapassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkamiṃsu. "
msgstr "Then they got up from their seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha Kassapa, keeping him on their right, before leaving. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya11, pts-vp-pli2.49, sc6
msgctxt "mn81:11.1"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, jotipālo māṇavo ghaṭikāraṃ kumbhakāraṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Jotipāla said to Ghatīkāra, "

msgctxt "mn81:11.2"
msgid "‘imaṃ nu tvaṃ, samma ghaṭikāra, dhammaṃ suṇanto atha ca pana agārasmā anagāriyaṃ na pabbajissasī’ti? "
msgstr "‘Dear Ghaṭīkāra, you have heard this teaching, so why don’t you go forth from the lay life to homelessness?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:11.3"
msgid "‘Nanu maṃ, samma jotipāla, jānāsi, andhe jiṇṇe mātāpitaro posemī’ti? "
msgstr "‘Don’t you know, dear Jotipāla, that I look after my blind old parents?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:11.4"
msgid "‘Tena hi, samma ghaṭikāra, ahaṃ agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajissāmī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Well then, dear Ghaṭīkāra, I shall go forth from the lay life to homelessness.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya12
msgctxt "mn81:12.1"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, ghaṭikāro ca kumbhakāro jotipālo ca māṇavo yena kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho, ānanda, ghaṭikāro kumbhakāro kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Ghaṭīkāra and Jotipāla went to the Buddha Kassapa, bowed and sat down to one side. Ghaṭīkāra said to the Buddha Kassapa, "

msgctxt "mn81:12.2"
msgid "‘ayaṃ me, bhante, jotipālo māṇavo sahāyo piyasahāyo. "
msgstr "‘Sir, this is my dear friend Jotipāla, a brahmin student. "

msgctxt "mn81:12.3"
msgid "Imaṃ bhagavā pabbājetū’ti. "
msgstr "Please give him the going forth.’ "

msgctxt "mn81:12.4"
msgid "Alattha kho, ānanda, jotipālo māṇavo kassapassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa santike pabbajjaṃ, alattha upasampadaṃ. "
msgstr "And Jotipāla the brahmin student received the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya13, pts-vp-pli2.50, sc7
msgctxt "mn81:13.1"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho acirūpasampanne jotipāle māṇave aḍḍhamāsupasampanne vegaḷiṅge yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena bārāṇasī tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi. "
msgstr "Not long after Jotipāla’s ordination, a fortnight later, the Buddha Kassapa—having stayed in Vebhaliṅga as long as he wished—set out for Benares. "

msgctxt "mn81:13.2"
msgid "Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena bārāṇasī tadavasari. "
msgstr "Traveling stage by stage, he arrived at Benares, "

msgctxt "mn81:13.3"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ, ānanda, kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho bārāṇasiyaṃ viharati isipatane migadāye. "
msgstr "where he stayed near Benares, in the deer park at Isipatana. "

#. REF: nya14
msgctxt "mn81:14.1"
msgid "Assosi kho, ānanda, kikī kāsirājā: ‘kassapo kira bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho bārāṇasiṃ anuppatto bārāṇasiyaṃ viharati isipatane migadāye’ti. "
msgstr "King Kikī of Kāsi heard that he had arrived. "

#. VAR: bhadrāni yānāni yojāpetvā bhadraṃ → bhadraṃ bhadraṃ (mr)
msgctxt "mn81:14.2"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, kikī kāsirājā bhadrāni bhadrāni yānāni yojāpetvā bhadraṃ yānaṃ abhiruhitvā bhadrehi bhadrehi yānehi bārāṇasiyā niyyāsi mahaccarājānubhāvena kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ dassanāya. "
msgstr "He had the finest carriages harnessed. He then mounted a fine carriage and, along with other fine carriages, set out in full royal pomp from Benares to see the Buddha Kassapa. "

msgctxt "mn81:14.3"
msgid "Yāvatikā yānassa bhūmi yānena gantvā yānā paccorohitvā pattikova yena kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
msgstr "He went by carriage as far as the terrain allowed, then descended and approached the Buddha Kassapa on foot. He bowed and sat down to one side. "

msgctxt "mn81:14.4"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho, ānanda, kikiṃ kāsirājānaṃ kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi. "
msgstr "The Buddha educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired him with a Dhamma talk. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:14.5"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, kikī kāsirājā kassapena bhagavatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena dhammiyā kathāya sandassito samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then King Kikī said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "mn81:14.6"
msgid "‘adhivāsetu me, bhante, bhagavā svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghenā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Sir, would the Buddha together with the mendicant Saṅgha please accept tomorrow’s meal from me?’ "

msgctxt "mn81:14.7"
msgid "Adhivāsesi kho, ānanda, kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho tuṇhībhāvena. "
msgstr "The Buddha Kassapa consented in silence. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya15
msgctxt "mn81:15.1"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, kikī kāsirājā kassapassa bhagavato sammāsambuddhassa adhivāsanaṃ viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi. "
msgstr "Then, knowing that the Buddha had consented, King Kikī got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before leaving. "

# NOTE: The description of the dish is unique, and uncertain. BB’s “rice in the sheaf”—based on comm—is hardly possible. Mudika in the sense of “soft” is the simplest reading (cf. sukaramaddava), while pandu may well refer to a yellowish colored “saffron” rice such as is common in India today.
#. REF: nya16
#. VAR: paṇḍupuṭakassa → paṇḍumuṭikassa (bj, pts1) | paṇḍumudikassa (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn81:16.1"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, kikī kāsirājā tassā rattiyā accayena sake nivesane paṇītaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyādāpetvā paṇḍupuṭakassa sālino vigatakāḷakaṃ anekasūpaṃ anekabyañjanaṃ, kassapassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa kālaṃ ārocāpesi: "
msgstr "And when the night had passed, King Kikī had a variety of delicious foods prepared in his own home—soft saffron rice with the dark grains picked out, served with many soups and sauces. Then he had the Buddha informed of the time, saying, "

msgctxt "mn81:16.2"
msgid "‘kālo, bhante, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Sir, it’s time. The meal is ready.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya17, pts-vp-pli2.51, sc8
msgctxt "mn81:17.1"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena kikissa kāsirañño nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghena. "
msgstr "Then Kassapa Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went to the home of King Kikī, where he sat on the seat spread out, together with the Saṅgha of mendicants. "

msgctxt "mn81:17.2"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, kikī kāsirājā buddhappamukhaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappesi sampavāresi. "
msgstr "Then King Kikī served and satisfied the mendicant Saṅgha headed by the Buddha with his own hands with a variety of delicious foods. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:17.3"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, kikī kāsirājā kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ bhuttāviṃ onītapattapāṇiṃ aññataraṃ nīcaṃ āsanaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
msgstr "When the Buddha Kassapa had eaten and washed his hand and bowl, King Kikī took a low seat and sat to one side. "

msgctxt "mn81:17.4"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho, ānanda, kikī kāsirājā kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "There he said to the Buddha Kassapa, "

msgctxt "mn81:17.5"
msgid "‘adhivāsetu me, bhante, bhagavā bārāṇasiyaṃ vassāvāsaṃ; "
msgstr "‘Sir, may the Buddha please accept my invitation to reside in Benares for the rainy season. "

# NOTE: The king is promising that the offerings for the whole sangha in the vassa will be just as luxurious as the ones just offered. This statement echoes the Buddha’s statement near the end of the sutta, Evarūpo ca, mahārāja, ghaṭikāro kumbhakāro. The Buddha is emphasizing that it is the qualities of trust and conduct that he cares about in a lay devotee, not the luxury of the offerings.
msgctxt "mn81:17.6"
msgid "evarūpaṃ saṅghassa upaṭṭhānaṃ bhavissatī’ti. "
msgstr "The Saṅgha will be looked after in the same style.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:17.7"
msgid "‘Alaṃ, mahārāja. "
msgstr "‘Enough, great king. "

msgctxt "mn81:17.8"
msgid "Adhivuttho me vassāvāso’ti. "
msgstr "I have already accepted an invitation for the rains residence.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:17.9"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho, ānanda … "
msgstr "For a second time … "

msgctxt "mn81:17.10"
msgid "tatiyampi kho, ānanda, kikī kāsirājā kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "and a third time King Kikī said to the Buddha Kassapa, "

msgctxt "mn81:17.11"
msgid "‘adhivāsetu me, bhante, bhagavā bārāṇasiyaṃ vassāvāsaṃ; "
msgstr "‘Sir, may the Buddha please accept my invitation to reside in Benares for the rainy season. "

msgctxt "mn81:17.12"
msgid "evarūpaṃ saṅghassa upaṭṭhānaṃ bhavissatī’ti. "
msgstr "The Saṅgha will be looked after in the same style.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:17.13"
msgid "‘Alaṃ, mahārāja. "
msgstr "‘Enough, Great King. "

msgctxt "mn81:17.14"
msgid "Adhivuttho me vassāvāso’ti. "
msgstr "I have already accepted an invitation for the rains residence.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:17.15"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, kikissa kāsirañño ‘na me kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho adhivāseti bārāṇasiyaṃ vassāvāsan’ti ahudeva aññathattaṃ, ahu domanassaṃ. "
msgstr "Then King Kikī, thinking, ‘The Buddha does not accept my invitation to reside for the rains in Benares,’ became sad and upset. "

msgctxt "mn81:17.16"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, kikī kāsirājā kassapaṃ bhagavantaṃ arahantaṃ sammāsambuddhaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then King Kikī said to the Buddha Kassapa, "

msgctxt "mn81:17.17"
msgid "‘atthi nu kho, bhante, añño koci mayā upaṭṭhākataro’ti? "
msgstr "‘Sir, do you have another attendant better than me?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya18, pts-vp-pli2.52, sc9
msgctxt "mn81:18.1"
msgid "‘Atthi, mahārāja, vegaḷiṅgaṃ nāma gāmanigamo. "
msgstr "‘Great king, there is a market town named Vebhaliṅga, "

msgctxt "mn81:18.2"
msgid "Tattha ghaṭikāro nāma kumbhakāro; "
msgstr "where there’s a potter named Ghaṭīkāra. "

msgctxt "mn81:18.3"
msgid "so me upaṭṭhāko aggupaṭṭhāko. "
msgstr "He is my chief attendant. "

#. VAR: attheva → atthi (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn81:18.4"
msgid "Tuyhaṃ kho pana, mahārāja, na me kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho adhivāseti bārāṇasiyaṃ vassāvāsanti attheva aññathattaṃ, atthi domanassaṃ. "
msgstr "Now, great king, you thought, “The Buddha does not accept my invitation to reside for the rains in Benares,” and you became sad and upset. "

#. VAR: ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa → ghaṭikāre kumbhakāre (bj, s2, s3, km) | ghaṭīkāre kumbhakāre (s1, pts1)
msgctxt "mn81:18.5"
msgid "Tayidaṃ ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa natthi ca na ca bhavissati. "
msgstr "But Ghaṭīkāra doesn’t get upset, nor will he. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:18.6"
msgid "Ghaṭikāro kho, mahārāja, kumbhakāro buddhaṃ saraṇaṃ gato, dhammaṃ saraṇaṃ gato, saṃghaṃ saraṇaṃ gato. "
msgstr "Ghaṭīkāra has gone for refuge to the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "mn81:18.7"
msgid "Ghaṭikāro kho, mahārāja, kumbhakāro pāṇātipātā paṭivirato, adinnādānā paṭivirato, kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato, musāvādā paṭivirato, surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato. "
msgstr "He doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, lie, or take alcoholic drinks that cause negligence. "

msgctxt "mn81:18.8"
msgid "Ghaṭikāro kho, mahārāja, kumbhakāro buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato, dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato, saṃghe aveccappasādena samannāgato, ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato. "
msgstr "He has experiential confidence in the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha, and has the ethics loved by the noble ones. "

msgctxt "mn81:18.9"
msgid "Ghaṭikāro kho, mahārāja, kumbhakāro dukkhe nikkaṅkho, dukkhasamudaye nikkaṅkho, dukkhanirodhe nikkaṅkho, dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya nikkaṅkho. "
msgstr "He is free of doubt regarding suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation. "

msgctxt "mn81:18.10"
msgid "Ghaṭikāro kho, mahārāja, kumbhakāro ekabhattiko brahmacārī sīlavā kalyāṇadhammo. "
msgstr "He eats in one part of the day; he’s celibate, ethical, and of good character. "

# NOTE: The same phrases is said of samana sakyaputta at SN 42.10
msgctxt "mn81:18.11"
msgid "Ghaṭikāro kho, mahārāja, kumbhakāro nikkhittamaṇisuvaṇṇo apetajātarūparajato. "
msgstr "He has set aside gems and gold, and rejected gold and money. "

# NOTE: For musala, BB has “pick”. Clearly it is a digging implement of some kind. See https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/on-the-austerities/3837
#. VAR: kumbhakāro pannamusalo na sahatthā pathaviṃ khaṇati → kumbhakāro na musalena na sahatthā paṭhaviñca khanati (s1-3, km) | kumbhakāro na musalena na sahatthā paṭhaviṃ khaṇati (pts1) | kumbhakāro na musalena sahatthā pathaviñca khaṇati (mr)
msgctxt "mn81:18.12"
msgid "Ghaṭikāro kho, mahārāja, kumbhakāro pannamusalo na sahatthā pathaviṃ khaṇati. "
msgstr "He’s put down the shovel and doesn’t dig the earth with his own hands. "

#. VAR: mūsikukkaro → mūsikukkāro (bj) | mūsikukkuro (si, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn81:18.13"
msgid "Yaṃ hoti kūlapaluggaṃ vā mūsikukkaro vā taṃ kājena āharitvā bhājanaṃ karitvā evamāha: "
msgstr "He takes what has crumbled off by a riverbank or been dug up by mice, and brings it back in a carrier. When he has made a pot, he says, "

msgctxt "mn81:18.14"
msgid "“ettha yo icchati taṇḍulapaṭibhastāni vā muggapaṭibhastāni vā kaḷāyapaṭibhastāni vā nikkhipitvā yaṃ icchati taṃ haratū”ti. "
msgstr "“Anyone may leave bagged sesame, mung beans, or chickpeas here and take what they wish.” "

msgctxt "mn81:18.15"
msgid "Ghaṭikāro kho, mahārāja, kumbhakāro andhe jiṇṇe mātāpitaro poseti. "
msgstr "He looks after his blind old parents. "

msgctxt "mn81:18.16"
msgid "Ghaṭikāro kho, mahārāja, kumbhakāro pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko tattha parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā. "
msgstr "And since he has ended the five lower fetters, Ghaṭīkāra will be reborn spontaneously and will become extinguished there, not liable to return from that world. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya19, sc10
msgctxt "mn81:19.1"
msgid "Ekamidāhaṃ, mahārāja, samayaṃ vegaḷiṅge nāma gāmanigame viharāmi. "
msgstr "This one time, great king, I was staying near the market town of Vebhaliṅga. "

msgctxt "mn81:19.2"
msgid "Atha khvāhaṃ, mahārāja, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa mātāpitaro tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa mātāpitaro etadavocaṃ: "
msgstr "Then I robed up in the morning and, taking my bowl and robe, went to the home of Ghaṭīkāra’s parents, where I said to them, "

# NOTE: Bhaggava doesn’t mean “potter”, but rather “fire-master”.
msgctxt "mn81:19.3"
msgid "“handa ko nu kho ayaṃ bhaggavo gato”ti? "
msgstr "“Excuse me, where has Bhaggava gone?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:19.4"
msgid "“Nikkhanto kho te, bhante, upaṭṭhāko antokumbhiyā odanaṃ gahetvā pariyogā sūpaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjā”ti. "
msgstr "“Your attendant has gone out, sir. But take rice from the pot and sauce from the pan and eat.” "

#. VAR: pakkamiṃ → pakkāmiṃ (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn81:19.5"
msgid "Atha khvāhaṃ, mahārāja, kumbhiyā odanaṃ gahetvā pariyogā sūpaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamiṃ. "
msgstr "So that’s what I did. And after eating I got up from my seat and left. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:19.6"
msgid "Atha kho, mahārāja, ghaṭikāro kumbhakāro yena mātāpitaro tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā mātāpitaro etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Ghaṭīkāra went up to his parents and said, "

msgctxt "mn81:19.7"
msgid "“ko kumbhiyā odanaṃ gahetvā pariyogā sūpaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkanto”ti? "
msgstr "“Who took rice from the pot and sauce from the pan, ate it, and left?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:19.8"
msgid "“Kassapo, tāta, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho kumbhiyā odanaṃ gahetvā pariyogā sūpaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkanto”ti? "
msgstr "“It was the Buddha Kassapa, my dear.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:19.9"
msgid "Atha kho, mahārāja, ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Ghaṭīkāra thought, "

msgctxt "mn81:19.10"
msgid "“lābhā vata me, suladdhaṃ vata me, "
msgstr "“I’m so fortunate, so very fortunate, "

msgctxt "mn81:19.11"
msgid "yassa me kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho evaṃ abhivissattho”ti. "
msgstr "in that the Buddha Kassapa trusts me so much!” "

#. VAR: na vijahati → na vijahi (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn81:19.12"
msgid "Atha kho, mahārāja, ghaṭikāraṃ kumbhakāraṃ aḍḍhamāsaṃ pītisukhaṃ na vijahati, sattāhaṃ mātāpitūnaṃ. "
msgstr "Then joy and happiness did not leave him for a fortnight, or his parents for a week. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya20, pts-vp-pli2.53, sc11
msgctxt "mn81:20.1"
msgid "Ekamidāhaṃ, mahārāja, samayaṃ tattheva vegaḷiṅge nāma gāmanigame viharāmi. "
msgstr "Another time, great king, I was staying near that same market town of Vebhaliṅga. "

msgctxt "mn81:20.2"
msgid "Atha khvāhaṃ, mahārāja, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa mātāpitaro tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa mātāpitaro etadavocaṃ: "
msgstr "Then I robed up in the morning and, taking my bowl and robe, went to the home of Ghaṭīkāra’s parents, where I said to them, "

msgctxt "mn81:20.3"
msgid "“handa ko nu kho ayaṃ bhaggavo gato”ti? "
msgstr "“Excuse me, where has Bhaggava gone?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:20.4"
msgid "“Nikkhanto kho te, bhante, upaṭṭhāko anto kaḷopiyā kummāsaṃ gahetvā pariyogā sūpaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjā”ti. "
msgstr "“Your attendant has gone out, sir. But take porridge from the pot and sauce from the pan and eat.” "

msgctxt "mn81:20.5"
msgid "Atha khvāhaṃ, mahārāja, kaḷopiyā kummāsaṃ gahetvā pariyogā sūpaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamiṃ. "
msgstr "So that’s what I did. And after eating I got up from my seat and left. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:20.6"
msgid "Atha kho, mahārāja, ghaṭikāro kumbhakāro yena mātāpitaro tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā mātāpitaro etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Ghaṭīkāra went up to his parents and said, "

msgctxt "mn81:20.7"
msgid "“ko kaḷopiyā kummāsaṃ gahetvā pariyogā sūpaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkanto”ti? "
msgstr "“Who took porridge from the pot and sauce from the pan, ate it, and left?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:20.8"
msgid "“Kassapo, tāta, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho kaḷopiyā kummāsaṃ gahetvā pariyogā sūpaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkanto”ti. "
msgstr "“It was the Buddha Kassapa, my dear.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:20.9"
msgid "Atha kho, mahārāja, ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Ghaṭīkāra thought, "

msgctxt "mn81:20.10"
msgid "“lābhā vata me, suladdhaṃ vata me, "
msgstr "“I’m so fortunate, so very fortunate, "

msgctxt "mn81:20.11"
msgid "yassa me kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho evaṃ abhivissattho”ti. "
msgstr "to be trusted so much by the Buddha Kassapa!” "

msgctxt "mn81:20.12"
msgid "Atha kho, mahārāja, ghaṭikāraṃ kumbhakāraṃ aḍḍhamāsaṃ pītisukhaṃ na vijahati, sattāhaṃ mātāpitūnaṃ. "
msgstr "Then joy and happiness did not leave him for a fortnight, or his parents for a week. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya21, pts-vp-pli2.54, sc12
msgctxt "mn81:21.1"
msgid "Ekamidāhaṃ, mahārāja, samayaṃ tattheva vegaḷiṅge nāma gāmanigame viharāmi. "
msgstr "Another time, great king, I was staying near that same market town of Vebhaliṅga. "

#. VAR: kuṭi → gandhakuṭi (bj) | kuṭī (pts1)
msgctxt "mn81:21.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena kuṭi ovassati. "
msgstr "Now at that time my hut leaked. "

msgctxt "mn81:21.3"
msgid "Atha khvāhaṃ, mahārāja, bhikkhū āmantesiṃ: "
msgstr "So I addressed the mendicants, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:21.4"
msgid "“gacchatha, bhikkhave, ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa nivesane tiṇaṃ jānāthā”ti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, go to Ghaṭikāra’s home and find some grass.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:21.5"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, mahārāja, te bhikkhū maṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "When I said this, those mendicants said to me, "

#. VAR: āvesane → āvesanaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn81:21.6"
msgid "“natthi kho, bhante, ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa nivesane tiṇaṃ, atthi ca khvāssa āvesane tiṇacchadanan”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, there’s no grass there, but his workshop has a grass roof.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:21.7"
msgid "“Gacchatha, bhikkhave, ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa āvesanaṃ uttiṇaṃ karothā”ti. "
msgstr "“Then go to the workshop and strip the grass.” "

msgctxt "mn81:21.8"
msgid "Atha kho te, mahārāja, bhikkhū ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa āvesanaṃ uttiṇamakaṃsu. "
msgstr "So that’s what they did. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:21.9"
msgid "Atha kho, mahārāja, ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa mātāpitaro te bhikkhū etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then Ghaṭīkāra’s parents said to those mendicants, "

msgctxt "mn81:21.10"
msgid "“ke āvesanaṃ uttiṇaṃ karontī”ti? "
msgstr "“Who’s stripping the grass from the workshop?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:21.11"
msgid "“Bhikkhū, bhagini, kassapassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa kuṭi ovassatī”ti. "
msgstr "“It’s the mendicants, sister. The Buddha’s hut is leaking.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:21.12"
msgid "“Haratha, bhante, haratha, bhadramukhā”ti. "
msgstr "“Take it, sirs! Take it, my dears!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:21.13"
msgid "Atha kho, mahārāja, ghaṭikāro kumbhakāro yena mātāpitaro tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā mātāpitaro etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Ghaṭīkāra went up to his parents and said, "

msgctxt "mn81:21.14"
msgid "“ke āvesanaṃ uttiṇamakaṃsū”ti? "
msgstr "“Who stripped the grass from the workshop?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:21.15"
msgid "“Bhikkhū, tāta, kassapassa kira bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa kuṭi ovassatī”ti. "
msgstr "“It was the mendicants, dear. It seems the Buddha’s hut is leaking.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:21.16"
msgid "Atha kho, mahārāja, ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Ghaṭīkāra thought, "

msgctxt "mn81:21.17"
msgid "“lābhā vata me, suladdhaṃ vata me, "
msgstr "“I’m so fortunate, so very fortunate, "

msgctxt "mn81:21.18"
msgid "yassa me kassapo bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho evaṃ abhivissattho”ti. "
msgstr "to be trusted so much by the Buddha Kassapa!” "

msgctxt "mn81:21.19"
msgid "Atha kho, mahārāja, ghaṭikāraṃ kumbhakāraṃ aḍḍhamāsaṃ pītisukhaṃ na vijahati, sattāhaṃ mātāpitūnaṃ. "
msgstr "Then joy and happiness did not leave him for a fortnight, or his parents for a week. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: na devotivassi → na cātivassi (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn81:21.20"
msgid "Atha kho, mahārāja, āvesanaṃ sabbantaṃ temāsaṃ ākāsacchadanaṃ aṭṭhāsi, na devotivassi. "
msgstr "Then the workshop remained with the sky for a roof for the whole three months, but no rain fell on it. "

msgctxt "mn81:21.21"
msgid "Evarūpo ca, mahārāja, ghaṭikāro kumbhakāro’ti. "
msgstr "And that, great king, is what Ghaṭīkāra the potter is like.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:21.22"
msgid "‘Lābhā, bhante, ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa, suladdhā, bhante, ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa "
msgstr "‘Ghaṭīkāra the potter is fortunate, very fortunate, "

msgctxt "mn81:21.23"
msgid "yassa bhagavā evaṃ abhivissattho’ti. "
msgstr "to be so trusted by the Buddha Kassapa.’ "

# NOTE: While supeyyam might seem to mean “sauce ingredients”, and is translated as “sauce materials” by BB, it is always used in the sense of “sauce”, eg at SN 47.8. The phrase tadupiyañca sūpeyyaṃ recurs at DN 17 and SN 22.96 where it must also refer to “sauce”. This means that the food that is sent is cooked food, not, as one might assume from the quantity, dry foodstuffs. This in turn supports the rejection of paṇḍupuṭaka in the sense of “rice in the sheaf”.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya22, sc13
msgctxt "mn81:22.1"
msgid "Atha kho, ānanda, kikī kāsirājā ghaṭikārassa kumbhakārassa pañcamattāni taṇḍulavāhasatāni pāhesi paṇḍupuṭakassa sālino tadupiyañca sūpeyyaṃ. "
msgstr "Then King Kikī sent around five hundred cartloads of rice, soft saffron rice, and suitable sauce to Ghaṭīkāra. "

msgctxt "mn81:22.2"
msgid "Atha kho te, ānanda, rājapurisā ghaṭikāraṃ kumbhakāraṃ upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then one of the king’s men approached Ghaṭīkāra and said, "

msgctxt "mn81:22.3"
msgid "‘imāni kho, bhante, pañcamattāni taṇḍulavāhasatāni kikinā kāsirājena pahitāni paṇḍupuṭakassa sālino tadupiyañca sūpeyyaṃ. "
msgstr "‘Sir, these five hundred cartloads of rice, soft saffron rice, and suitable sauce have been sent to you by King Kikī of Kāsī. "

#. VAR: paṭiggaṇhathā’ti → patigaṇhātūti (bj, pts1) | paṭiggaṇhātūti (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn81:22.4"
msgid "Tāni, bhante, paṭiggaṇhathā’ti. "
msgstr "Please accept them.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn81:22.5"
msgid "‘Rājā kho bahukicco bahukaraṇīyo. "
msgstr "‘The king has many duties, and much to do. "

msgctxt "mn81:22.6"
msgid "Alaṃ me. "
msgstr "I have enough. "

msgctxt "mn81:22.7"
msgid "Raññova hotū’ti. "
msgstr "Let this be for the king himself.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya23
msgctxt "mn81:23.1"
msgid "Siyā kho pana te, ānanda, evamassa: "
msgstr "Ānanda, you might think: "

msgctxt "mn81:23.2"
msgid "‘añño nūna tena samayena jotipālo māṇavo ahosī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Surely the brahmin student Jotipāla must have been someone else at that time?’ "

msgctxt "mn81:23.3"
msgid "Na kho panetaṃ, ānanda, evaṃ daṭṭhabbaṃ. "
msgstr "But you should not see it like this. "

msgctxt "mn81:23.4"
msgid "Ahaṃ tena samayena jotipālo māṇavo ahosin”ti. "
msgstr "I myself was the student Jotipāla at that time.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "mn81:23.5"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "mn81:23.6"
msgid "Attamano āyasmā ānando bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandīti. "
msgstr "Satisfied, Venerable Ānanda was happy with what the Buddha said. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn81:23.7"
msgid "Ghaṭikārasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

